data.event: Georgetown takes its name from George Kennedy, who settled in the area in 1821.

data.event: By 1650, the once plentiful Hurons had been wiped out by European diseases, and the Iroquois.

data.event: The region was now open to the Algonquian Ojibwa (also known as Mississauga), who moved in.

event.title: 1850 the remaining Mississauga natives were removed

data.event: By 1850 the remaining Mississauga natives were removed to the Six Nations reserve, where the New Credit Reserve was established.
Commencing in 1781, the British government purchased blocks of land from the Mississauga Nation.
In 1818, they purchased land that later became the townships of Esquesing and Nassagaweya.
